[Flutter: What’s next on the Web?](https://medium.com/flutter/flutter-whats-next-on-the-web-e0454bff964)

> It’s important that Flutter web apps feel natural on the web. This includes features such as scrolling behavior, text functionality, splash screens, hyperlinks, SEO, and other web-specific UI features.

@Hixie while the post didn't really answer anything about SEO and only mention it, still lead to me thinking that it's high priority. I feel there's quite a lot of people picking other frameworks while the only thing they miss from Flutter Web is the SEO functionality but it's such a vital thing they just cannot do without it.

> If anyone is interested I just published https://pub.dev/packages/seo which does address the previously mentioned cloaking issue as the html is always in the body. Currently package supports only converting widget tree to html but I'm planning to look into adding meta tag support too.

@krokyze would you recommend to use your package alongside [meta_seo](https://pub.dev/packages/meta_seo) to improve even more the SEO of the web?

EDIT: With v 0.2 of the seo package, support for meta tags was added. So, I don't think there is any reason to use meta_seo package.
